Dole ne Amurka ta ninka kudaden da take baiwa AI.
Saboda kasar Sin ta kara shiga harkar kere kere, ya kamata Amurka ta ninka kudaden da za ta kashe wajen gudanar da bincike a fannin, in ji mai zuba jari kuma mai aikin A2 Kai-Fu Lee, wanda ya yi aiki a Google, Microsoft da Apple.
Wannan furucin ya zo ne bayan da bangarori daban-daban na gwamnatin Amurka suka yi sanarwa game da AI, ko da yake Amurka gabaɗaya ba ta da dabarun AI na yau da kullun.
A halin yanzu, kasar Sin ta gabatar da shirin ta a bara: tana da burin zama kasa ta farko a kirkirar AI nan da shekarar 2030.
"Haɗa kudaden bincike na AI kyakkyawan farawa ne, ganin cewa duk sauran ƙasashe suna da nisa daga Amurka, kuma muna neman ci gaba na gaba a AI", in ji Lee.
Haɓaka kuɗin zai iya ninka damar da za a yi babban ci gaban AI a Amurka, Lee ya gaya wa CNBC a cikin wata hira da aka yi a ranar Lahadi.
Lea, marubucin littafin nan "AI Superpowers: China, Silicon Valley and the New World Order" an wallafa shi a wannan watan ne ta Houghton Mifflin Harcourt, Shugaba na Sinovation Ventures, wanda ya riga ya zuba jari a daya daga cikin manyan kamfanonin AI na kasar Sin, Face++.
A shekarun 1980 a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon ya tsara tsarin AI wanda ya doke mafi kyawun dan wasan Othello na Amurka, kuma daga baya ya yi aiki a matsayin mai zartarwa a Microsoft Research da kuma shugaban Google China.
Lee ya amince da gasar fasahar gwamnatin Amurka da ta gabata kamar Challenge Robotics for Advanced Defense Research Project kuma ya tambayi lokacin da za a gudanar da ayyukan gaba, don taimakawa wajen gano mai hangen nesa na gaba.
