Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da 'yi wa mutane barazana' ta hanyar 'tallan farfaganda'
Mako guda bayan da jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani talla na shafuffuka hudu a wata jaridar Amurka da ke ambaton amfanin cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka wajen yada farfaganda.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump a ranar Laraba ya yi magana game da biyan kudin da ake biyan China Daily a Des Moines Register - jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a jihar Iowa - bayan da ya zargi kasar Sin da kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, zargin da kasar Sin ta musanta.
Zargin Trump na cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka, wanda jami'an Amurka suka fada wa Reuters, wani sabon mataki ne a cikin wani yunkuri na kara matsin lamba da Washington ke yi kan kasar Sin.
Ko da yake al'ada ce ga gwamnatoci na ƙasashen waje su saka talla don su inganta kasuwanci, a yanzu haka Beijing da Washington suna cikin faɗaɗa yaƙin cinikayya, wanda ya sa suke ɗaga harajin kayayyakin da suke shigowa da su.
An tsara takunkumin da China ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya don cin zarafin masu fitar da kayayyaki a jihohi kamar Iowa da ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican Trump, in ji masana na China da Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa China, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikata, manoma da 'yan kasuwa na Amurka lahani.
China, Branstad ta rubuta wani ra'ayi a cikin Des Moines Register a ranar Lahadi, "yanzu muna ninka wannan barazanar ta hanyar gudanar da tallace-tallace na farfaganda a cikin kafofin watsa labarai na kyauta".
"A cikin yaɗa ta'addancinsa, gwamnatin Sin ta yi amfani da al'adun 'yancin magana da 'yancin 'yan jarida da ake daraja sosai a Amurka ta hanyar saka tallace-tallace masu biya a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A akasin haka, a kantunan sayar da jaridu na titi a nan, a Beijing, za ku ga takunkumi ga muryoyin daban-daban kuma ba za ku ga ainihin tunani na ra'ayoyi daban-daban da mutanen Sin za su iya yi game da yanayin tattalin arzikin China ba, saboda kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin ikon Jam'iyyar Kwaminis ta Sin", in ji shi.
Ya ƙara da cewa "ɗaya daga cikin manyan kafofin watsa labarai a China ta ƙi tayin buga" labarinsa, ko da yake bai ambata ba.
